to the editor re pinochet case reviving voices of the tortured front page jan 3 the arrest of gen augusto pinochet in 1998 has led to increased openness and healing in chile while contributing to the consolidation of chilean democracy unfortunately the american government has remained silent on this case asserting that it must balance the pursuit of accountability and justice with the possible harm the case might do to chile 's democratic transition our government can not remain neutral about whether a former dictator responsible for the death or disappearance of more than 3000 people and the torture of 40000 should stand trial a luxury that general pinochet 's victims never enjoyed the globalization of justice for human rights violators as illustrated by the pinochet case should be celebrated as a landmark achievement stacie jonas washington jan 3 2000

